item.title: Thalaina angulosa
item.dc:creator: andrewbrown
item.description: Thalaina angulosa which is not in the data base. These moths are very similar to Clara's Satin moth. "The forewing pattern is similar to that of Thalaina clara but that has a straight brown line from the costa to tornus, whereas Thalaina angulosa has a straight brown line from the base to near the middle of the margin." from-http://lepidoptera.butterflyhouse.com.au/naco/angulosa.html
